properties.Name: DunBradstreetPaymentIndex
properties.Description:
The Dun And Bradstreet Payment Index gives an objective assessment of the speed with which a company pays its invoices. 

The Index corresponds to the average number of days after the due date (or the number of days beyond agreed terms) for the company. The payment performance forms the basis of the Payment Index. 

D&B Payment Index  =  Payment behavior  [in days beyond agreed terms]
----------------------------------------------------------------- 
100 = Anticipating
90 = With discount
80 = On time
70 =15 days delayed
60 = 22 days delayed
50 = 30 days delayed
40 = 60 days delayed
30 = 90 days delayed
20 = 120 days delayed
UN = Not available

Columns.Name: DunBradstreetPaymentIndexId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Dun Bradstreet Payment Index.

Columns.Name: DunBradstreetPaymentIndexDescription
Columns.Description: The description of the Dun Bradstreet Payment Index.
